<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Bankview </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Located to the west of the densely populated district of Beltline in the inner city,
                Bankview is a beautiful residential neighborhood in South West Calgary. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">First established as a community in 1908, Bankview underwent a major redesign during the
                early fifties giving rise to the development of several high-density apartment buildings in the area.
            </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Established in the 1880’s by William Nimmons for ranching and farming, the housing
                shortage and economic boom during the early 1900’s is how Bankview became a part of Calgary, being fully
                purchased in 1908. </p>
            <p class="par-xl">After a major redesign in the 1950’s, Bankview is now a higher density apartment area.</p>

        </div>
